        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 2:02PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 201 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Alcova, which is 19 miles southwest of Casper,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Natrona County, including the following locations... Casper Mountain
and Casper Mountain County Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
